CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 10, 1955, pg. B4, reads: "New Diamond Market Crowd - This is but a part of the huge crowd of people that flocked to the New Diamond Market, 211 Diamond Street, Tuesday night to participate in giant give-away contest. Disc Jockey Mary Dee, shown left, bending under the WHOD microphone, emceed the show.  Among the prizes are two 1956 Plymonuth [sic] sedans, two Sylvania TV sets, two Norge refrigerators and hundreds of lesser prizes. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: WHOD radio disc jockey Mary Dee handing item to woman, in Diamond Market with balloons advertising cheese and neon sign "We Sell Irish"
